Content Platform System Management Help
The data type describes the resource. link links
link data type properties
The following table describes the properties included in the data type. link<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=185, y1=217, x2=1516, y2=2121
                   </p>
                   <div align="center"><table border="1" class="dataframe">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: right;">
      <th></th>
      <th>0</th>
      <th>1</th>
      <th>2</th>
      <th>3</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>0</th>
      <td>Property\nname</td>
      <td>Data type</td>
      <td>Description</td>
      <td>Notes</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>compression</td>
      <td>Boolean</td>
      <td>Specifies whether HCP should compress data before transmitting it to the other system\ninvolved in the replication link. For an active/active link, this setting applies to data being\nreplicated in both directions on the link.\nValid values are:\ntrue\nHCP should compress data.\nfalse\nHCP should not compress data.\nThe default is false.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>connection</td>
      <td>connection</td>
      <td>Identifies the remote system for the replication link and specifies how the two systems\nshould communicate with each other.</td>
      <td>This property is required on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>description</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies a description of the replication link. This description is optional. The default is no\ndescription.\nTo remove a description from an existing link, specify the description property with no value.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>4</th>
      <td>encryption</td>
      <td>Boolean</td>
      <td>Specifies whether HCP should encrypt data before transmitting it to the other system\ninvolved in the replication link. For an active/active link, this setting applies to data being\nreplicated in both directions on the link.\nValid values are:\ntrue\nHCP should encrypt data.\nfalse\nHCP should not encrypt data.\nThe default is false.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>5</th>
      <td>failoverSettings</td>
      <td>failover\nSettings</td>
      <td>Specifies the automatic failover and failback settings for the replication link.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>6</th>
      <td>id</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the system-supplied unique ID for the replication link. HCP generates this ID\nautomatically when you create a link.</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request. It\nis returned only by a verbose GET request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>7</th>
      <td>name</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the name of the replication link. Link names must be from one through 64\ncharacters long and can contain any valid UTF-8 characters, including white space. Link\nnames are not case sensitive.\nLink names must be unique within a replication topology.</td>
      <td>This property is required on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>8</th>
      <td>priority</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies whether priority should be given to objects with the oldest changes, regardless of\nnamespace, or processing should be balanced across namespaces. For an active/active\nlink, this setting applies to both systems involved in the link.\nValid values are:\nFAIR\nBalance processing across namespaces.\nOLDEST_FIRST\nGive priority to objects with the oldest changes.\nThe default is OLDEST_FIRST.\nThese values are not case-sensitive.</td>
      <td>This property is optional on a PUT request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>9</th>
      <td>statistics</td>
      <td>statistics</td>
      <td>Specifies information about activity on the replication link.</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request. It\nis returned only by a verbose GET request.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>10</th>
      <td>status</td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Specifies the general state of the replication link. Possible values are:\nGOOD\nThe link is healthy.\nWARNING\nThe link is healthy, but normal replication is not occurring on the link.\nBAD\nThe link is unhealthy.</td>
      <td>This property is not valid on a PUT or POST request. It\nis returned only by a verbose GET request.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></div>
